OL,3,CPhoto ID rules may have stopped
OL,4,C445,000 casting ballot, poll suggests
OL,6,FAround 450,000 people may have been
OL,7,Fturned away from polling booths in the
OL,8,FGeneral Election because they didn't
OL,9,Fbring the correct identification,
OL,10,Ffigures have suggested.
OL,12,FMore in Common, who organised the
OL,13,Fpoll, found 3.2% of around 2,000
OL,14,Fpeople surveyed were denied the
OL,15,Fopportunity to vote at least once
OL,16,Fbecause they lacked the right ID.
OL,18,FThey used these numbers to estimate
OL,19,Fmore than 850,000 people across the UK
OL,20,Fmay have had the same experience.
