OL,3,CPhoto ID rules may have stopped
OL,4,C445,000 casting ballot, poll suggests
OL,6,FMore than half of these people -
OL,7,F445,000 - either gave up or returned
OL,8,Fand were still unable to vote.
OL,10,FThursday's General Election marked the
OL,11,Ffirst time in the UK where bringing a
OL,12,Fvalid form of ID was a requirement to
OL,13,Freceive a ballot paper.
OL,15,FNot all types of photo ID were
OL,16,Faccepted at polling stations, but
OL,17,Famong the permitted forms were
OL,18,Fpassports, driving licences or blue
OL,19,Fbadges.
