OL,3,CPhoto ID rules may have stopped
OL,4,C445,000 casting ballot, poll suggests
OL,6,FThe poll found that a third of people
OL,7,Fturned away had ID which was not on
OL,8,Fthe list of valid ID, a quarter said
OL,9,Fthe name on their ID was different
OL,10,Ffrom that listed on the electoral
OL,11,Fregister, while 12% said they were
OL,12,Ftold the picture on their ID did not
OL,13,Fmatch their appearance.
OL,15,FEthnic minorities were
OL,16,Fdisproportionately affected, and were
OL,17,Ftwice as likely to be turned away than
OL,18,Fwhite people.
