OL,3,CPhoto ID rules may have stopped
OL,4,C445,000 casting ballot, poll suggests
OL,6,FThe survey found that 6.5% of voters
OL,7,Fof colour said they were turned away,
OL,8,Fcompared with 2.5% of white voters.
OL,10,FAlba Kapoor, head of policy at the
OL,11,FRunnymede Trust think tank, said: "As
OL,12,Fwe warned, these voter ID laws are
OL,13,Fdiscriminatory by design; and must be
OL,14,Fscrapped.
OL,16,F"They are an attack on the democratic
OL,17,Frights of people of colour, and leave
OL,18,Fpeople without a say in the running of
OL,19,Four country."
