OL,3,CPhoto ID rules may have stopped
OL,4,C445,000 casting ballot, poll suggests
OL,6,FPhoto ID rules were brought in by
OL,7,FBoris Johnson's government as part of
OL,8,Fthe Elections Act 2022, as the then-
OL,9,Fgovernment said they were necessary to
OL,10,Fcombat the risk of in-person voter
OL,11,Ffraud.
OL,13,FThe requirements were first enforced
OL,14,Fat the May 2023 local council
OL,15,Felections in England.
OL,17,FJohnson was himself turned away from a
OL,18,Fpolling station after forgetting to
OL,19,Fbring a photo ID in May's local
OL,20,Felections.
